<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:212px;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger,_China,_Anonym,_um_1875.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger,_China,_Anonym,_um_1875.jpg/210px-Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger,_China,_Anonym,_um_1875.jpg" width="210" height="162" class="thumbimage" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger%2C_China%2C_Anonym%2C_um_1875.jpg/315px-Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger%2C_China%2C_Anonym%2C_um_1875.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger%2C_China%2C_Anonym%2C_um_1875.jpg/420px-Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger%2C_China%2C_Anonym%2C_um_1875.jpg 2x" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Drei_Frauen_am_Pranger,_China,_Anonym,_um_1875.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="http://bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Three women in the <a href="Pillory" title="Pillory">pillory</a>, <a href="China" title="China">China</a></div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Criminology</b> (from <a href="Latin" title="Latin">Latin</a> <span lang="la" xml:lang="la"><i>crīmen</i></span>, "accusation"; and <a href="Ancient_Greek" title="Ancient Greek">Greek</a> <span lang="grc" xml:lang="grc">-λογία</span>, <i><a href="-logy" title="-logy">-logia</a></i>) is the scientific study of the nature, extent, causes, and control of criminal behavior in both the individual and in society. Criminology is an interdisciplinary field in the <a href="Behavioral_sciences" title="Behavioral sciences" class="mw-redirect">behavioral sciences</a>, drawing especially upon the research of <a href="Sociology" title="Sociology">sociologists</a> (particularly in the <a href="Sociology_of_deviance" title="Sociology of deviance" class="mw-redirect">sociology of deviance</a>), <a href="Psychology" title="Psychology">psychologists</a> and <a href="Psychiatry" title="Psychiatry">psychiatrists</a>, <a href="Social_anthropology" title="Social anthropology">social anthropologists</a> as well as on writings in <a href="Law" title="Law">law</a>.</p>
<p>Areas of research in criminology include the incidence, forms, causes and consequences of crime, as well as social and governmental regulations and reaction to crime. For studying the distribution and causes of crime, criminology mainly relies upon <a href="Quantitative_methods_in_criminology" title="Quantitative methods in criminology">quantitative methods</a>. The term <i>criminology</i> was coined in 1885 by Italian law professor <a href="Raffaele_Garofalo" title="Raffaele Garofalo">Raffaele Garofalo</a> as <i>criminologia</i>. Later, French anthropologist <a href="Paul_Topinard" title="Paul Topinard">Paul Topinard</a> used the analogous French term <i>criminologie</i>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table id="toc" class="toc">
<tr>
<td>
